<%- @title = "About" %>

<div id=about" class="static_page">
  <p>
    <h3>About</h3>
    Redactify is a twitter front-end for a user's timeline with tweets with specified tags redacted as to not spoil events that
    a user might not be able to watch in real time.
  </p>

  <p>
    <h3>Redactify is written and maintained by</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><%= auto_link("Dan McNevin - dpmcnevin@redactify.com") %></li>
    </ul>
  </p>
      

  <p>
    <h3>Redactify is open source</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><%= link_to "Redactify GitHub repository", "http://github.com/dpmcnevin/redactify" %></li>
      <li><%= link_to "Fork of twitter-auth", "http://github.com/dpmcnevin/twitter-auth" %></li>
    </ul>
  </p>

  <p>
    <h3>Follow us on Twitter</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><%= "#{auto_link_twitter("@redactify")} - System updates and status".html_safe %></li>
      <li><%= "#{auto_link_twitter("@mental_thinking")} - Dan McNevin".html_safe %></li>
    </ul>
  </p>

  <p>
    <h3>Acknowledgments</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><%= link_to "Twitter", "http://twitter.com" %></li>
      <li><%= link_to "Ruby on Rails", "http://rubyonrails.com" %></li>
      <li><%= link_to "Heroku", "http://heroku.com" %></li>
      <li><%= "Michael Bleigh's #{link_to "twitter_auth", "http://github.com/mbleigh/twitter-auth"} gem.".html_safe %></li>
    </ul>
  </p>
</div>
